      "description": "One-loop scalar box integral $I_B$ for 2-to-2 scattering of two distinct massive scalars (matter lines of mass $m_1$ and $m_2$) exchanging gravitons in the t-channel. Two opposite edges are massless (graviton exchanges) and two opposite edges are massive matter propagators of masses $m_1$ and $m_2$. Used as one of the basis integrals (with crossed-box, triangle, and triangle-down) in the reduction of the one-loop four-point amplitude in Eq. (Org_Scalar_Integrals). Result is taken from the literature (Beenakker-Denner) and expanded in the classical (small-$q$) limit; the box is more singular than classical so subleading terms in the polarization-to-spin map must be retained. The relevant nonrelativistic 3D form used in the EFT matching is given near Eq. (4.49).",
